'''Kristian Aadnevik''' (born 10 January 1978) is a London-based Norwegian fashion designer, who graduated from [[Royal College of Art]] in 2002.<ref name="norway1">{{cite web|url=http://www.norway.org.uk/News_and_events/culture/fashion/kristian/ |title=Nicole Kidman, if you're reading this; here's your man! |publisher=Norway.org.uk |date= |accessdate=7 April 2013}}</ref>

==Early life and education==
Aadnevik was born in Bergen, Norway. After finishing an education at Bergen Yrkesskole he moved to London to pursue a MA at the [[Royal College of Art]], where he received numerous awards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.norskdesign.no/2006/from-valdres-to-vogue-contemporary-norwegian-fashion-design-article3386-7659.html |title=From Valdres to Vogue – Contemporary Norwegian fashion design – Norwegian Design Council |publisher=Norskdesign.no |date=30 July 2006 |accessdate=7 April 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121118084232/http://www.norskdesign.no/2006/from-valdres-to-vogue-contemporary-norwegian-fashion-design-article3386-7659.html |archivedate=18 November 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> During his studies he worked as a design assistant at [[Alexander McQueen]].<ref>Feldman, Jenny (November 2007) "Foreign Exchange". ''Nylon'', p.48</ref>

== Career ==
[[File:Kristian Aadnevik backstage SS13.jpg|thumb|left|Kristian Aadnevik backstage SS13| Kristian Aadnevik backstage SS14 [[London Fashion Week]]]]
Aadnevik established his own label in 2004<ref name="norway1"/> and he presented his first collection the same year at [[London Fashion Week]].<ref name="norway1"/> Apart from his own label he has collaborated and designed collections for several international brands including Charles Jourdan Paris for Japan,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.norway.org.uk/News_and_events/culture/fashion/aadnevik_ss08/ |title=Aadnevik presents new collection at LFW |publisher=Norway.org.uk |date=15 September 2007 |accessdate=7 April 2013}}</ref> Harrods International<ref>{{cite web|author=in Fashion, Fashiontribes, TrendAlert |url=http://fashiontribes.typepad.com/fashion/2008/01/new-fashion-des.html |title=New Fashion Design Names to Know Hit the Catwalk in Italy – Fashion Blog &#124; Fashion Tribes Blog |publisher=Fashiontribes.typepad.com |date=15 January 2008 |accessdate=7 April 2013}}</ref> as well as held a position as a senior designer at [[Roberto Cavalli]].<ref name="autogenerated1">{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-proteges-to-unveil-looks-471119?full=true |title=Fashion 'Proteges' to Unveil Looks – Fashion Features – Fashion |publisher=WWD.com |date=10 January 2008 |accessdate=7 April 2013}}</ref>

In 2007 Aadnevik was chosen as one of five designers in "The Protégé Project", an initiative of Australian Wool innovation,<ref name="autogenerated1"/> which resulted in him being selected protégé of [[Donatella Versace]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elleuk.com/fashion/designers-to-know/node_187598#image=1 |title=Kristian Aadnevik selected protégé of Donatella Versace; Elleuk.com |publisher=Elleuk.com |date= |accessdate=}}</ref> In line with this he showcased his F/W 2008 collection at [[Milan Fashion Week]] where his collection was met with critical acclaim and he was named as one of fall 2008's most promising new talents by [[Style.com]].

Aadnevik has dressed several celebrities, some of them include [[Beyoncé]], [[Nicole Scherzinger]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ellequebec.com/celebrites/nicole-scherzinger-une-prestation-remarquee/a/64891 |title=Nicole Scherzinger in Kristian Aadnevik X Factor &#124; Ellequebec.com |publisher=Ellequebec.com |date= |accessdate=7 April 2013}}</ref> [[Selena Gomez]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://coolspotters.com/actresses/selena-gomez/and/brands/kristian-aadnevik#medium-3220137 |title=Selena Gomez in Kristian Aadnevik in her Come & Get It music video &#124; Coolspotters.com |publisher=Coolspotters.com |date= |accessdate=7 April 2013}}</ref> [[Kelly Rowland]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://coolspotters.com/musicians/kelly-rowland/and/clothing/kristian-aadnevik-fall-2007-dress#medium-651060 |title=Kelly Rowland and Kristian Aadnevik Fall 2007 Dress &#124; Coolspotters.com |publisher=Coolspotters.com |date= |accessdate=7 April 2013}}</ref> [[Cheryl Cole]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.graziadaily.co.uk/fashion/archive/2008/12/08/cheryl-s-saturday-night-dress-watch.htm |title=Cheryl's Saturday-night dress watch &#124; Grazia Fashion |publisher=Graziadaily.co.uk |date=8 December 2008 |accessdate=7 April 2013}}</ref> [[Britney Spears]],<ref>Ihenacho, Francis (February 2007)"Kristian Aadnevik". ''Vangard'', p.123</ref> [[Rihanna]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://coolspotters.com/musicians/rihanna/and/brands/kristian-aadnevik/media/1571155#medium-1571155 |title=Rihanna in Kristian Aadnevik You Magazine}}</ref> [[Pixie Lott]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.promonews.tv/2010/02/15/pixie-lott’s-gravity-by-nick-frew/ Pixie Lott’s Gravity by Nick Frew |title=Pixie Lott in Kristian Aadnevik |publisher=Promonews.tv |date= |accessdate= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100217081153/http://www.promonews.tv/2010/02/15/pixie-lott%E2%80%99s-gravity-by-nick-frew/ |archivedate=17 February 2010 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> [[Daisy Lowe]] and [[Dita Von Teese]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.alomoda.ro/inna-la-rma-2010-in-kristian-aadnevik.html |title=Inna la RMA 2010 in Kristian AadnevikAloModa &#124; AloModa |publisher=Alomoda.ro |date=22 July 2010 |accessdate=7 April 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310105850/http://www.alomoda.ro/inna-la-rma-2010-in-kristian-aadnevik.html |archivedate=10 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> British Musician [[Estelle (musician)|Estelle]] also wore one of his creations in the music video for her single "[[American Boy]]".<ref>http://women.timesonline.co.uk/tol/life_and_style/women/fashion/article6133506.ece</ref>
